Equatorial view
 This page shows you the area in the sky around the celestial equator including the zoodiac as seen from earth. The short lines coming from the solar system objects show the future positions of the objects:
 moon: 1 day; 
 sun, mercury, venus: 1 week;
 mars: 2 weeks;
 jupiter, saturn: 1 month;
 uranus, neptune: 1 year. 
 The brown curve shows you the horizon for your location and time.
 You may scale the region around a planet to get a magnified field of view up to 2°.
